trans-unit.source: Ball tree and KD tree query time will become slower as \(k\) increases. This is due to two effects: first, a larger \(k\) leads to the necessity to search a larger portion of the parameter space. Second, using \(k > 1\) requires internal queueing of results as the tree is traversed.
trans-unit.target: 随着\（k \）的增加，球树和KD树的查询时间将变慢。这是由于两个影响：首先，较大的\（k \）导致必须搜索较大部分的参数空间。其次，使用\（k> 1 \）要求遍历树时对结果进行内部排队。

trans-unit.source: Ball tree and KD tree query times can be greatly influenced by data structure. In general, sparser data with a smaller intrinsic dimensionality leads to faster query times. Because the KD tree internal representation is aligned with the parameter axes, it will not generally show as much improvement as ball tree for arbitrarily structured data.
trans-unit.target: 球树和KD树的查询时间会受到数据结构的极大影响。通常，具有较小固有维数的稀疏数据将导致更快的查询时间。因为KD树的内部表示与参数轴对齐，所以对于任意结构化的数据，它通常不会显示出比球形树那么大的改进。

trans-unit.source: KD tree query time changes with \(D\) in a way that is difficult to precisely characterise. For small \(D\) (less than 20 or so) the cost is approximately \(O[D\log(N)]\), and the KD tree query can be very efficient. For larger \(D\), the cost increases to nearly \(O[DN]\), and the overhead due to the tree structure can lead to queries which are slower than brute force.
trans-unit.target: KD树查询时间以\（D \）改变，难以精确表征。对于较小的\（D \）（小于20左右），成本大约为\（O [D \ log（N）] \），并且KD树查询可以非常有效。对于较大的\（D \），成本增加到接近\（O [DN] \），并且由于树结构而导致的开销可能导致查询的速度比蛮力慢。

trans-unit.source: Algorithm description:

Algorithm description: The messages sent between points belong to one of two categories. The first is the responsibility \(r(i, k)\), which is the accumulated evidence that sample \(k\) should be the exemplar for sample \(i\). The second is the availability \(a(i, k)\) which is the accumulated evidence that sample \(i\) should choose sample \(k\) to be its exemplar, and considers the values for all other samples that \(k\) should be an exemplar. In this way, exemplars are chosen by samples if they are (1) similar enough to many samples and (2) chosen by many samples to be representative of themselves.
trans-unit.target: 算法描述：点之间发送的消息属于两类之一。第一个是责任\（r（i，k）\），它是样本\（k \）应该是样本\（i \）的典范的累积证据。第二个是可用性\（a（i，k）\），它是样本\（i \）应该选择样本\（k \）为其示例的累积证据，并考虑所有其他样本的值\ （k \）应该是一个示例。以这种方式，如果样本（1）与许多样本足够相似，并且（2）由许多样本选择以代表自己，则它们由样本选择。

Multiclass classification means a classification task with more than two classes; e.g., classify a set of images of fruits which may be oranges, apples, or pears. Multiclass classification makes the assumption that each sample is assigned to one and only one label: a fruit can be either an apple or a pear but not both at the same time.

trans-unit.source: Multiclass classification: classification task with more than two classes. Each sample can only be labelled as one class.

Multilabel classification assigns to each sample a set of target labels. This can be thought as predicting properties of a data-point that are not mutually exclusive, such as topics that are relevant for a document. A text might be about any of religion, politics, finance or education at the same time or none of these.
trans-unit.target: 多标签分类为每个样本分配了一组目标标签。可以将其视为预测不互斥的数据点属性，例如与文档相关的主题。文字可能同时涉及宗教，政治，金融或教育中的任何一个，或者都不涉及任何一个。

trans-unit.source: Multilabel classification: classification task labelling each sample with x labels from n_classes possible classes, where x can be 0 to n_classes inclusive. This can be thought of as predicting properties of a sample that are not mutually exclusive. Formally, a binary output is assigned to each class, for every sample. Positive classes are indicated with 1 and negative classes with 0 or -1. It is thus comparable to running n_classes binary classification tasks, for example with sklearn.multioutput.MultiOutputClassifier. This approach treats each label independently whereas multilabel classifiers may treat the multiple classes simultaneously, accounting for correlated behavior among them.

Multioutput regression assigns each sample a set of target values. This can be thought of as predicting several properties for each data-point, such as wind direction and magnitude at a certain location.
trans-unit.target: 多输出回归为每个样本分配一组目标值。可以将其视为预测每个数据点的多个属性，例如某个位置的风向和大小。

trans-unit.source: Multioutput regression: predicts multiple numerical properties for each sample. Each property is a numerical variable and the number of properties to be predicted for each sample is greater than or equal to 2. Some estimators that support multioutput regression are faster than just running n_output estimators.

Multioutput-multiclass classification (also known as multitask classification): classification task which labels each sample with a set of non-binary properties. Both the number of properties and the number of classes per property is greater than 2. A single estimator thus handles several joint classification tasks. This is both a generalization of the multilabel classification task, which only considers binary attributes, as well as a generalization of the multiclass classification task, where only one property is considered.

Multioutput-multiclass classification and multi-task classification means that a single estimator has to handle several joint classification tasks. This is both a generalization of the multi-label classification task, which only considers binary classification, as well as a generalization of the multi-class classification task. The output format is a 2d numpy array or sparse matrix.
trans-unit.target: 多输出多类分类和多任务分类意味着单个估计器必须处理多个联合分类任务。这既是对仅考虑二进制分类的多标签分类任务的概括，也是对多类分类任务的概括。输出格式为2d numpy数组或稀疏矩阵。

trans-unit.source: Randomness of the underlying implementations: The underlying implementations of SVC and NuSVC use a random number generator only to shuffle the data for probability estimation (when probability is set to True). This randomness can be controlled with the random_state parameter. If probability is set to False these estimators are not random and random_state has no effect on the results. The underlying OneClassSVM implementation is similar to the ones of SVC and NuSVC. As no probability estimation is provided for OneClassSVM, it is not random.
trans-unit.target: 基础实现的随机性： SVC 和 NuSVC 的基础实现仅使用随机数生成器来随机整理数据以进行概率估计（当 probability 设置为 True 时）。可以使用 random_state 参数控制此随机性。如果将 probability 设置为 False ,则这些估计量不是随机的， random_state 对结果没有影响。底层的 OneClassSVM 实现类似于 SVC 和 NuSVC 的实现。由于没有为 OneClassSVM 提供概率估计，它不是随机的。

A Bagging classifier is an ensemble meta-estimator that fits base classifiers each on random subsets of the original dataset and then aggregate their individual predictions (either by voting or by averaging) to form a final prediction. trans-unit.source: A Gaussian mixture model is a probabilistic model that assumes all the data points are generated from a mixture of a finite number of Gaussian distributions with unknown parameters. One can think of mixture models as generalizing k-means clustering to incorporate information about the covariance structure of the data as well as the centers of the latent Gaussians.
trans-unit.target: 高斯混合物模型是一种概率模型,它假设所有的数据点都是由有限数量的高斯分布的混合物产生的,参数未知。我们可以认为混合模型是对k-means聚类的概括,纳入了数据的协方差结构以及潜高斯中心的信息。

trans-unit.source: A clustering result satisfies completeness if all the data points that are members of a given class are elements of the same cluster.
